      "content": "i mean, what about the more militant groups or the stuff that wasn't so \"strategic\" or \"legal\"? like, i've heard people say that without the more radical/violent stuff happening, the government wouldn't have actually listened to the nonviolent stuff. was the nonviolent path actually the main reason things changed, or do you think that's just how it's usually taught?",
